<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distinguished by the stiff, spreading white hairs of the calyx and stems combined with the narrow white corolla, which is funnel-shaped above a long basal cylindrical tube. The peduncles are often long and the sepals very short, often c. 5 mm long.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
